  <title translate="true">Tip #11</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Heading3"><text styleclass="Heading3" translate="true">Tip of the Day</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:58px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">If you get into a mess with hundreds of windows, you can clear them all away at one fell swoop with the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Panic</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> icon (Munch&apos;s Scream) in the &#160;main </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">System Folder</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> window.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">In future, you may wish to avoid creating loads of top-level tool windows. Take a look at the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Idea Space</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, which you can use to group together several tools while you follow a train of thought.</text><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
  </body>
